The paper deals with data structures for maintaining vertex cover and matching in a dynamic graph, which are fundamental problems in graph theory and algorithms. The techniques used involve data structures, algorithms, and combinatorics, which are all relevant to the aforementioned sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
